<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>love seat <i>(UK)</i> • love seat <i>(U.S.)</i></xh5><p> <i>love seat (UK)—</i>a seat or bench which accommodates two people facing in opposite directions: The term “<u>love seat</u>” more often refers to a curious S-shaped two-seater, with the sitters facing opposite directions (paradoxically). I’ve never heard of a standard two-seater couch called a “love seat”...</p><p> <i>love seat (U.S.)—</i>a small sofa or couch designed for two occupants: The original master bedroom of the mansion offers a large room with canopy bed, sitting area and <u>love seat</u> facing the fireplace.</p> </entry>
